reviewText: Exactly what we were looking for.

If your looking at getting this, you already know what it is.  The new version is a bit cheesy, but your not buying it for the second one so no worries.

Saw part of this movie years ago, late at night. Never caught the name. Finally saw it again last year. Now it's mine, mine, mine all mine. One of the greatest love stories ever told.right up there with African Queen, Turandot, Moonstruck, Chocolat, The King of Hearts, Sita Sings the Blues & Cyrano D'Bergerac.
Wow, what a beautiful movie! When I looked at the cover I thought for sure it would be more of a child's movie, but I was very impressed. Sweet story line, it is one of my favorites
